  "market_context": "Previous Friday formed a reversal and expansion candle, setting up Monday–Wednesday upward expansion. Thursday countered the range with a candle-2 closure and hourly change in state of delivery (CISD), signaling a bearish reversal for Friday continuation toward weekly open.",
  "key_observation": "Only the bearish side of the Thursday reversal had an hourly change in state of delivery, making the low unreliable and confirming bearish bias for Friday.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified previous Friday as a reversal and expansion candle, establishing expectation of early-week continuation higher.",
    "Step 2: Noted Monday–Wednesday expansion away from weekly structure, with Wednesday reaching into a fair value gap containing failure swings.",
    "Step 3: Observed Thursday forming a candle-2 closure at the upper range, but emphasized that only the bearish side showed hourly change in state of delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 4: Concluded the low was not protected due to lack of CISD on bullish side, thus favoring short entries targeting Friday continuation lower toward weekly open.",
    "Step 5: Dropped to hourly chart to confirm the CISD on the bearish side as the decisive factor for trade bias."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price moved lower on Friday as anticipated, confirming the successful Thursday counter setup.",
  "lessons": "Candle-2 closures alone are insufficient; hourly change in state of delivery (CISD) is required to validate the protected swing and determine which side of the reversal is tradable. Timeframe alignment (daily → hourly) is critical for confirmation.",
